com.hazelcast.jet

Interface IListJet<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of values maintained by this list
    All Superinterfaces:
    Collection<E>, DistributedObject, ICollection<E>, IList<E>, Iterable<E>, List<E>

    public interface IListJet<E>
extends IList<E>
    A concurrent, in-memory concurrent list implementation.

    In comparison to IMapJet, the entries of the list are only stored on a single partition, and as such adding more nodes will not add more storage capacity to the list. While IMap doesn't provide any ordering, the items in IListJet are ordered.

    It's possible to use the link as a data source or sink in a Jet Pipeline, using Sources.list(String) or Sinks.list(String).

    See Also:
    IList, Sources.list(String), (String)
